These descriptions have made it possible to compare precisely the Brazilian colonies with material from North Atlantic and Adriatic. Both English and Adriatic ephebic specimens differ from those found in shallowwater localities of the West Atlantic in the presence of 10 pairs of short, short-spaced lateral spines, and deeper (about 0.2 mm ), wider zooids (about 0.28 mm wide) connected by longer proximal tubes.
